content: I‚Äôm a user of both SmoothSync for Cloud Calendar and SmoothSync for Cloud Contacts.  LOVE THEM BOTH!!!  I got a message on my BusyCal app (on my apple computer) that we have to set up ‚ÄúTwo Factor Authentication‚Äù for our apps through Apple ID by June 15.  I did that for for my Apple computer relatively easily, but my Samsung devices proved to be a little more challenging.  For whatever reason, I COULD NOT simply ‚Äúupdate" my newly generated password from Apple ID.  For your convenience, this is the process that finally worked for me:   1.  Set up Two Factor Authentication on the Apple ID WEBSITE FIRST  2.  Generate a new password assigned for apple computer/apps   3.  Generate a new password (separate) for Android/iOS Apps (one for each app)  4.  DELETE the SmoothSync account(s) on your IOS device  5.  ADD a new account using your Apple ID (username) and the newly generated password associated to it.    Hope this was useful.

Thank you for making an app that dependably does what I've been trying to do for years: Reliably sync appointments over multiple platforms. A change on any of them quickly shows up on them all! I use Outlook on a PC, iCal on my MacBook Pro, the iPad calender, the calender app on my Verizon iPhone 4s and the calendar app on my AT&T Galaxy S3. I use each of them in my business and personal life. I already had iCloud syncing on everything but the Android S3. The key to getting SmoothSync working there was when I set an appointment (event/task) on the Android, in the window that opens when you start that, choose the right calendar, not the native Android calendar but the one that matches up to your email.Test it by going to one date and set an appt using one of the calendar choices you have and name the appt that email. Then go to another date and set an appointment using any other calendar or email and name the appt that calendar/email. Keep doing this with any calendars that show up in the calendar box. Then go back to the SmoothSync app and sync. Then go to your other devices and refresh the calendar and see which appt shows. Then set appts on your other devices & check Android.
